    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nahua hairstyle of postclassic central Mexico in which some or all of the hair on the sides of the scalp is shaved.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
